 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">For willingness to donate, we found that there was a significant three-way interaction [
  <span class="italic">G</span>
  <span class="sup">2</span>(4) = 12.37, 
  <span class="italic">p</span> = 0.02]. However, we did not find a difference in the willingness to donate between liberals and conservatives in the temperature condition (
  <span class="italic">X</span>
  <span class="sup">2</span> = 0.97, 
  <span class="italic">p</span> = 0.32) or in the neutral condition (
  <span class="italic">X</span>
  <span class="sup">2</span> = 2.65, 
  <span class="italic">p</span> = 0.10) (
  <a rid="tab1" ref-type="table" href="#tab1">Table 1</a>). The null results in donation could be driven by the fact that the donation question was hypothetical and no actual donations were made.
 </p>
